
Karen Gardias has been music teacher at Davis Senior High School Davis High School since 1993 and has directed the Davis High School Madrigal Singers Madrigals during that time.  In 2000 she initiated the Advanced Treble Choir (ATC) as the fourth singing group at the high school and received the Harmony in Our Lives Award in 2005.   She is a graduate of http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Baldwin_Wallace_Conservatory_of_Music BaldwinWallace Conservatory of Music, is a member of Phi Kappa Phi and Phi Delta Kappa, holds a masters degree from http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maryville_University Maryville University and a Ph.D. from the http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/University_of_the_Pacific_(United_States) University of the Pacific.

